SIMPLE: fragrant
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fragrant
<hw>Fra"grant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fragrans</ets>. <ets>-antis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>fragrare</ets> to
emit a smell of fragrance: cf. OF. <ets>fragrant</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Affecting the olfactory nerves agreeably; sweet of smell; odorous;
having or emitting an agreeable perfume.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Fragrant</qex> the fertile earth⟦br⟧
After soft showers.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Sweet-smelling; odorous; odoriferous;
sweet-scented; redolent; ambrosial; balmy; spicy; aromatic.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Fra"grant*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fraight</ent>⟦br⟧
